09:41.660 --> 09:47.060
and they are the ones that are actually the act is addressed to EU administrations from

09:47.060 --> 09:51.460
EU level until a member states local level.

09:51.460 --> 09:57.380
And it's all the binding requirements that are in the act go towards these public administrations.

09:57.380 --> 10:01.500
They don't go towards private parties.

10:01.500 --> 10:06.660
And those ones will decide together on certain solutions.

10:06.660 --> 10:08.980
And solutions is in a very broad term.

10:08.980 --> 10:14.540
So solutions can even be a framework, can be an architecture, can be guidelines, can also be a solution,

10:14.540 --> 10:19.100
can of course be software.

10:19.100 --> 10:22.580
Like the definition that is in the act is quite broad.

10:22.580 --> 10:28.620
But the public sector will agree in this interoperability governance on some solutions that will become interoperable

10:28.620 --> 10:33.620
Europe solutions so that everybody will not be, they don't have to reuse it,

10:33.620 --> 10:37.460
but they will at least need to look into the reuse of such solutions.

10:37.460 --> 10:45.740
